data.description: Priced to sell!  8 acres of Quiet solitude and amazing views  of the far off valley from this home off Blueridge Mountain Road just inside the Clarke County line from Loudoun County.  Main level bedroom and full bath with primary suite on the upper level.  Lower level offers additional space and an entertainment area.  Enjoy morning coffee on the covered front porch listening to the breeze through the tall trees in front.  Enjoy sunsets from the back deck looking west over the valley in  Clarke County,  Save on heat costs with 2 wood stoves and a 3rd one in the 2 car garage/ workshop. Build a fire in the masonry wood burning  fireplace.  Cook in the oversized kitchen with  granite counters and additional guest counter  seating. Wine fridge, stainless appliances,  fully vented stainless hood vent.  Ceramic tile throughout the kitchen area. 3 zoned heat and central air.  The land is mostly wooded with open space around the home for the back yard, garden and firepit area.  NO  HOA.  Large 2 car oversized extra tall garage with power. Huge machine shed for wood storage, boat storage etc. Scenic firepit area with views perfect for entertaining outdoors.  Large deer protected fenced garden.    Unfinished storage area in lower level with washer dryer.   Exterior is low maintenance vinyl siding and soffits.  Screened in deck area on side of home.  Easy access to Bears Den for hikes or the Appalachian Trail.  Minutes to Purcellville for grocers and restaurants. Enjoy local wineries and breweries nearby like Bluemont Station, Bears Chase or Dirt Farm.  Bluemont winery and so much more.   Easy access to Rt 7 and Rt 50 for commuting.  Internet is Starling for high speed or  T mobile hotspot, or Winchester Wireless . Watch the  video in tours section.
